caption: We're from out of the area and we were staying downtown and everything was just too fancy. We found wicker park and Pint was just the bar we were looking for. The servers/bartenders were super nice, the environment was nice and laid back, and the food was good. Had the wings.

I am so glad Pint reopened last month! This was our go to spot for over a year before the shut down this year. The new decor is nice. Our favorite server Rica is awesome and very attentive and knows what we love to order. Check it out.

I've been here multiple times on Wednesday Thursday and Friday night. Friday nights was surprisingly the quietest. LOVE this scholarly looking spot for happy hour and hosting events. I host alumni events across town and the Wellesbourne is ALWAYS a hit! The bartenders are lovely and the old management team (Charlotte) was super flexible but now the new guy didn't seem as caring of our group. The food is great when we get appetizers for the group. Location is perfect with parking across the street at the cinema.
Good was great and service was good. Atmosphere wasn't my favorite.
Best ever
Great food, good priced drinks and Amazing staff!

The food is always fresh and flavorful, staff members hands over great customer service. I liked how neat it is and character. Will come visit again.

A really fun bar to hang out, catch a game, have a beer which enjoying good company. Sitting outside during a warm summer night was my favorite time to visit. The sitting is along the sidewalk and busy Milwaukee ave so the great for people watching or just watching Chicago go by. The neighborhood is full of character and there's never a dull moment. Oh, the food is quite good too but of course the beers are what really count.

I really wanted to like the steak sandwich and the shepard's pie. my last time there was likely, in fact, our last time ever going. We had hairs in our beers. Food and beer is usually yummers. I get the Californian grilled cheese with avocado - the servers can be a little short but it's not a big deal whatsoever. Pint's fun for summer people watching too with their outdoor sidewalk patio. Also - they don't like it if you dine in the upstairs.

This place reminds me of one of my favorite pubs when I was in college at University of Illinois. It's laid back and servers are friendly. Prices are reasonable.

Worst way to end your fun day. Be careful, if you have more than 3 beers in 3 hours, the security might decide you had enough to drink. This is what happened just last Sunday, to my friend. He is a very low profile guy, I could say shy, and he always knows his place. But, for some reason I don't know or understand, the security said that he considers that my friend had enough to drink. I asked: "Did he bump into someone? Did he disturb anyone? Did he throw up anywhere? Make him walk a line." We didn't get an explanation, but what we got was threatenings with the police. Unfortunately, the pretty girl from the bar, I think her name is Paige, decided that if we could not get anymore drinks and have the tab closed, she should ignore us and be disrespectful, treating us like we were garbage. I was waving to her, she saw me, but choose to ignore me. When I called her again, she acted offended, although I should've been the one offended when you ignore me like that. Even if she couldn't serve us anymore, I don't think she had to have that kind of attitude. I am very disappointed. I also worked in bars, I know sometimes clients can be a pain, but this wasn't the case and I never treated my clients like that.
Every time I've had a positive experience. Good drink specials, an always interesting atmosphere, and some of the best wings I've ever had!

Been to a lot of bars and eateries in wicker park and gotta say Pint takes the cake. The staff was friendly and attentive. Stopped in on Sunday and the atmosphere is great. The outdoor area very entertaining. My girlfriend and I were offered a new drink creation by the establishment , on the house called sun tan lotion.  Dynamite drink. Will be returning to Pint

There are two parts to this bar and it's separated by a wall. One side is quiet and perfect for enjoying a peaceful drink; the other side is usually crowded and obnoxiously loud. It also has an upstairs area but I've never been to that part. The drinks are alright - not particularly strong, not particularly good. If you're looking for a quieter night out in Wicker Park, I suggest going here.
One of the few bars that seems to last in WP. In nicer weather, the patio is always bustling. Can do a lot worse in the summer.
Love the atmosphere. Like the beer selection. Food is only OK. Do not spend the extra dollars on the waygu burger ... I'm pretty sure it was just standard beef.

Their drink specials are great. $5 for a long island on a Sunday night. Entrees are pricier, but reasonable for the area. The portion sizes are fair--my side order of onion rings was very filling. Staff was a tad slow, so catch their attention if you need the check.
Love it!!!  Great atmosphere, great food and the portions are huge.  Definitely would suggest going here!
Pint always has really good music. The staff is pretty friendly and the artichoke dip is to die for.

The pint was a lovely place to have our first drink in the country. As tourists we didn't know what to expect in bars in a America but the staff, the food and the decor was all great. I would come back, but not so early.
their wraps, especially the chicken and goat cheese are the bomb.  Bloody mary's a plus.  Atmosphere great!
Love the martinis!

Really nice place to talk, music isn't too loud, nice beer.. Drafts around 5$, no cover.. No sketchy people like places around may have..  BUT it's too hot inside.. At least during summer :/

The pint was a lovely place to have our first drink in the country.  As tourists we didn't know what to expect in bars in a America but the staff, the food and the decor was all lovely.
